# TEMPORARY: the gh token lacks the `workflow` scope, so pushing .github/workflows/* is rejected.
# The CI config lives on disk at .github/workflows/ci.yml; once the scope is granted, force-add it
# (`git add -f .github/workflows/ci.yml`), remove this line, and push.
.github/

# Monorepo root ignores (OS / editor). Project-specific ignores live in each project's .gitignore.
.DS_Store
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log

# Claude Code — MACHINE-LOCAL ONLY. Deliberately NOT a blanket `.claude/` ignore: shared config
# (settings.json, skills/, commands/, agents/) is useful to anyone working on this repo with Claude
# and SHOULD stay committable. Only the two machine-specific things are excluded:
#   • worktrees/ are full recursive checkouts of this repo inside itself, complete with build
#     artifacts. They are untracked, so a stray `git add -A` from the main checkout would stage the
#     lot — this ignore is the guard against that.
#   • settings.local.json is per-machine by Claude Code's own `.local.` convention (an accumulated
#     Bash permission allowlist); on a PUBLIC repo it can also leak local paths and service names.
# Neither is left unprotected: both are captured for disaster recovery by the PRIVATE infra repo
# (~/workspace/domain_management/backup-infra.sh). Ignored here, backed up there.
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/settings.local.json
